race.comment: BRAZEN CRIME (3) is a progressive gelding for the Dryden & Snowden partnership. Chased gamely to just miss when resuming off 277 days at Canberra. Is sure to have come on from that and will appreciate having Heywood piloting. Should prove very tough to beat. LYSANDER (7) is knocking on the door, beaten narrowly in his last two. Boasts a terrific record over this journey and has enough pace to offset the wide alley. Should be in this for a long way. RIVERBEND UNICORN (11) closed nicely to arrive just in time to shed his maiden tag here last time. Full of confidence now and has gun hoop in Boudvillain booked to contest the wide draw. Expect to see him charging late. KOTAISHI (1) is ticking along nicely and is drawn to advantage. Can play a role in the finish. MISS STALWART (2) doesn't win out of turn but boasts peaks that can measure up. Keeping safe in exotics.
